Malt: Pale malt, Crystal Malt

Hops: CTZ, Centennial, Citra, Simcoe

A refreshing Lager, light on the palate and with a crisp finish. The addition of rice syrup results in a dry mouthfeel, with a small portion of the noble hop Saaz, to achieve a slightly herbal and earthy flavour.

Malt: Pale Malt, Rice Syrup, Carapils

Hops: Saaz

A light base crafted on Pale and Wheat malts, soured using our house strain of Lactobacillus, and generously dry hopped with passionfruit and mango. The initial taste is powerfully fruity, which rounds out
with the tart tang of the Sour style.

Malt: Pale, Wheat

Hops: Ella

beer.beer_name: Cookie Monsta White Choc Macadamia Golden Stout
beer.beer_description:
Prepare to be captivated by the enchanting fusion of flavours in our White Chocolate & Macadamia Golden Stout. A modern twist on the classic stout style, this golden-hued beauty surprises with its rich and roasty character, heightened by the indulgent additions of white chocolate and roasted macadamias. Get ready for a golden journey that challenges your perceptions of stouts.

Malt: Pale, Melanoidin, Rolled barley

Hops: Fuggles

Other: Chocolate Nibs, Vanilla Bean, Macadamias, Coffee Beans

Inspired by the pioneers of IPL’s in Europe through the 1800’s, this mid-strength lager with a burst of fruit flavours has been hopped to create an easy drinking brew. It’s one of our first and we think it will be around for a long time.

Malt: Pale Malt, Munich Malt, Honey Malt

Hops: Mittelfruh, Citra, Mosaic, Amarillo

This beer celebrates the one-year anniversary of our JOURNEY. The life we have lived, the laughs we have had, and the life lessons learnt. Enjoy a COLD IPA while you too reflect on the year that was….

Brewed with a portion of rice to provide a clean crisp finish that compliments the hop forward bitterness from a large whirlpool and dry hop addition. The US hops really bring this beer to the table, along with a reasonable 6.5% ABV.

Malt: Pale Ale Malt, Rolled Rice, Carapils

Hops: Amarillo, Cascade, Mosaic, Citra, Columbus

beer.beer_name: Bad Santa – Christmas Spiced Scotch Ale
beer.beer_description: Ginge spiced nose with golden brown gown & soft crown. Dry cit ginger malty smooth spicy mouthfeel.Dry spicy ginger easy drinking smooth finish

An easy-drinking crafty twist on a traditional Helles style mid-strength lager. Enjoy a balanced beer base of Pale and Munich with the added sweetness of Canadian Honey malt, rounded out with traditional European Noble hops.

Malt: Pale Malt, Munich Malt, Honey Malt

Hops: Hallertau Mittelfruh

Indulge your taste buds in the captivating allure of our Hazy IPA. Bursting with vibrant hop character and a luscious, juicy profile, this beer is a sensory adventure that will transport you to hop heaven. Prepare to embark on a journey of intense flavours and aromas that redefine what an IPA can be.

Malt: Pale, Wheat, Rolled oats, Light Crystal

Hops: Summit, Citra, Ella, Mosaic, Amarillo, El Dorado
Kiwi hazee lager is a masterful fusion of traditional lager craftsmanship and the vibrant fruity notes of new Zealand hops.
Fruity sour ale

Named the TroPOPical Pale after everyone’s favourite brewer and all-round excellent human, Neil “Pops” Whittorn, who sadly left us this year.  Pops gave us our wings in the craft beer industry, and now has his own watching over us all – no doubt enjoying a cold one or three with the angels. This limited-edition has a tropical fruit profile, including guava, passionfruit, mango and pineapple – smooth and naturally hazy with a refreshing finish.

Malt: Pale Malt, Wheat Malt, Rolled Oats, Carapils

Hops: Idaho 7, Nectaron, Taiheke, Nelson Sauvin
Tangy ginger beer brewed with fresh ginger and a touch of herb and spice.

Prepare your taste buds for an explosion experience with Juice Bomb, the hazy IPA that’s a flavour dynamo!

Picture a hazy golden blast zone, where mango, pineapple, and grapefruit collide in a taste explosion that’ll blow your taste buds away!

The velvet malt foundation brings a smoothness, making this a bombshell of flavour… A true taste adventure. Brace yourself for a finish that lingers, inviting you to savour the aftermath of this flavour explosion.

An historic beer style, this 3.5% farmhouse Saison is very sessionable, backed by raspberry, herbal and spicy flavours. It has a high carbonation but is gentle on the palette, lightly hopped to deliver soft citrus notes to compliment the fruit.

Malt: Pilsner, Wheat, Flaked Oats

Hops: Saaz

Other: Raspberry, Cassia Bark, Star Anise, Cardamom Pods
A fusion of fresh coconut and subtle lime create this taste sensation.
Refreshing, crisp apple taste with a spice aroma and modest pear finish.
